    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>A butterfly knife has a blade concealed between two halves of the handle that can be brought to bear quickly.</em></p>\n<p>If you are proficient with the butterfly knife (or have the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/feats/combat-feats/quick-draw-combat\">Quick Draw</a>&nbsp;feat) and are holding it in your hand, you may open it as a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Free-Actions\">free action</a>; a nonproficient user must spend a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Move-Actions\">move action</a>&nbsp;to open it. Otherwise, treat this weapon as a dagger. When itâ€™s closed, you gain a +2 bonus on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/sleight-of-hand\">Sleight of Hand</a>&nbsp;checks made to conceal it on your body.</p>",
